A Delta State House of Assembly aspirant, Udu Constituency, Hon. Chief Saturday Mofoye has promised to offer effective and efficient representation by bringing the dividends of democracy to his constituents if elected. Mofoye, a former Councillor, made the pledge when he suited his Expression of Interest and Nomination Forms to participate in the Delta State House of Assembly race under the platform of the Peoples Democrats Party, PDP, at the party’s state secretariat in Asaba. Mofoye, immediate past vice chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party, had obtained the form over two weeks ago, alongside his teeming supporters. The intending lawmaker, while speaking with newsmen, shortly after he submitted the form, said *I aspire to serve the good people of Udu state constituents at the Delta State House of Assembly. “I can assure you that our great party, the PDP will never regret choosing me to be the candidate to represent my people as accountability, transparency and good representation will be my watchword. “My intention is to serve through effective and efficient representation and by bringing the dividends of democracy to the people of Udu State Constituency. “I truly solicit for the support of my great party executives, caucuses and party faithful to enable me to emerge as the candidate for the election”, he said